RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Allowance Purse 27400. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 18 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since September 18 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considere d In Weight Allowances) NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAPTAIN CREED stalked off the rail the opening turn, challenged leaving the seven sixteenths pole and drew to even terms two deep toward the top of the stretch, dug in for the nod passing the sixteenth pole and gradually inched clear. SUSTENANCE took the lead at the three quarter pole and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure leaving the seven sixteenths, contested the edge nearest the rail on the far turn, was met toward the head of the lane and dug in at even terms, but relented inside the sixteenth pole. KASIMBA drifted out leaving the gate then rated close inside, picked up the chase approaching the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn, eased out leaving the turn and ran evenly in the stretch. MY HANDSOME MAN saved ground on the first turn then eased out into the backstretch, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the five path and finished evenly. YO VINNIE was shuffled back at the start then gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and showed little in the lane. MOSLEY NATURAL raced in the three path the first turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but flattened in the four path on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: My Handsome Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground 1st turn,chased 7/16,5p far turn,evenly lane

ENTRY.OWNER: Fanelli John and Longball Stables LLC

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 13700. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE MAY 18, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since May 18 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FLAT DISCOUNT settled in the three path the first turn, closed to the lead between horses nearing the five sixteenths pole, contested even terms at the rail into the far turn, took the nod midway through the turn and was steadily handled in the lane. CRUZ IN THE CASTLE angled in nearing the three quarter pole and rated the pace, was met approaching the five sixteenths pole, contested even terms two deep into the far turn, was met midway through the turn, dropped back past the eighth pole, flattened stride and held on for second. UNICORN SALLY raced off the rail on the opening turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path, cleared third nearing mid-stretch and was gaining on the runner-up. TIMEISGOLDEN came through the opening turn about the four path, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and ran evenly in the lane. TIZBIT rounded the first turn in the three path, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole and raced at the rail on the far turn and could only improve her position. AMERICA'S PRIDE raced with the pace inside but dropped back toward the half mile pole, gave chase approaching the three eighths, rounded the far turn near the rail and weakened. SOME IS NINE saved ground just off the early pace then eased out into the backstretch and gave chase from that point, raced in the four path on the far turn and weakened in the lane. ONEPRETTYTHING rounded the first turn in the four path, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole but showed little response. CALYPSO GHOST rounded the first turn off the rail, gave chase into the backstretch but weakened in the five path on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Flat Discount
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3p 1st turn,up between near 5/16,rail far turn,steady urging lane

ENTRY.NAME: Unicorn Sally
ENTRY.OWNER: Brooks Gerald E and Hess Jr Carl L

ENTRY.NAME: Cruz in the Castle
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,met near 5/16,even terms turn,flatten,held 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 62. Claiming Purse 11800. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. RACE.FOOTNOTES: RIDE THE RAPIDS stalked the early pace two deep then moved to even terms into the backstretch, dueled clear of And Whistle approaching the quarter pole and was steadily handled through the lane. MISS ANTIETAM raced in the three path the first turn, picked up the chase past the seven sixteenths pole and rounded the far turn at the rail, eased out leaving the turn and dueled through the stretch for second. DALLAS raced in the three path the first turn, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path and was outfinished in the stretch duel for second. LIL SPINNER saved ground, picked up the chase past the seven sixteenths pole and entered the far turn near the rail, checked off the heels of the waning And Whistle approaching the eighth pole, eased around that one leaving the turn and ran evenly in the lane. IMAGINE VICTORY rounded the first turn about the five path, left the turn outside and gave chase toward the three eighths pole, raced in the five path on the far turn and showed little in the lane. AND WHISTLE rated a slim lead inside, was met leaving the half mile pole and dueled from that point, but dropped back toward the quarter pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and weakened. HOVEL raced well back off the rail on the first turn and showed little response. HOLDING COURT rounded the first turn in the four path, gave chase from the three eighths pole but weakened past the five sixteenths.

ENTRY.OWNER: Lugamo Racing Stable LLC and J R Sanchez Racing Stable

RACE.FOOTNOTES: I'LLTAKECAREOFIT took an immediate lead and rated the pace inside, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and held well under steady stretch handling. NOCASHREFUNDS stalked from the four path the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole and raced off the rail on the far turn, dug in through the stretch and held on for second. GRUMPY'S BUDDY saved ground off the pace, bid nearing the three eighths pole and raced at the rail on the far turn, eased out past the eighth pole and finished evenly while closing the gap on the runner-up. STROLLINGINTHEWIND raced off the rail the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the three and four paths and ran evenly in the lane. DON'TCALLTOOEARLY rounded the first turn about the five path, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, angled to the five path through the far turn and showed little in the lane. REVEREND JACK rounded the opening turn in the three path, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole but weakened in the four path on the far turn. NEVERFOLD rated close inside on the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole but weakened off the rail on the far turn. JAZZ WITH DENIS came through the opening turn about the four path, raced well back outside into the backstretch and was eased.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 73. Allowance Purse 28400. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR WAIVER CLAIMING OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mil e Or Over Since October 18 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since September 18 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: REY O REYES rated a slim lead inside, was met at the three quarter pole and settled close from that point, recovered the advantage approaching the seven sixteenths, came under pressure toward the three eighths, raced at the rail on the far turn and dug in determinedly to hold off LIEUTENANT BROWN the final sixteenth. The latter steadied early then settled inside, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and remained a close factor to late stretch before relenting. AIR MEDAL saved ground well off the early pace, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail then dueled through the stretch and took third in the final yards. ESPRESSO rounded the opening turn in the four path then stalked from the seven eighths pole, took a brief lead at the three quarter but was met toward the seven sixteenths and gave chase from that point, rounded the far turn off the rail and flattened in the stretch duel for third. SUMMONING DENIS raced in the five path the opening turn, came though the second turn about the three path and picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the five path and finished evenly to close the gap. LEG UP stalked the early pace from the two and three paths, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path on the far turn and weakened. KAYLEE'S SPITFIRE was never a factor. O'RIGSBY settled in the three path, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole but faded through the backstretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Rey O Reyes
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated slim lead,met 3/4,rated close,up near 7/16,rail turn,drving

ENTRY.NAME: Air Medal
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,chased 7/16,off rail far turn,dueled,up 3rd late

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ZEN MASTER tapered in and stalked two deep, pulled himself to the lead approaching the three eighths pole and kept the edge through the backstretch, was urged nearing the quarter pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and was kept sharp to widen later yards. HOT FUDGE SONDE stalked from the four path the first turn, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and settled for second best. AZZARO STEEL raced in the four path the opening turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole and rounded the far turn in the three path, but showed little in the lane. SUBJECT TO CHANGE raced off the rail the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the six path and showed little more. RACE.RACE_TEXT: Randy Funkhouser Memorial S. CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 99. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR REGISTERED ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. $50 nominations close Wednesday, November 8, 2023. $50 to enter with a purse of $75,000 Added. Entries close Wednesday, November 15, 2023 by the usual time of closing. The added moni es and all fees to be divided 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth, and 3% to fifth. Weight: Three Year Olds 121 lbs.; Older 123 lbs. Field will be limited to ten starters with up to four alternates. Preference to those horses havi ng accumulated the highest 2022-2023 earnings at the time of closing of entries. Trophy to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NO CHANGE made light contact with Noballstwostrikes leaving the gate then saved ground, bid nearing the five sixteenths pole, angled to the three path and took the lead midway on the far turn and dug in under steady encouragement to hold on. SOCIAL CHIC raced off the pace in the three and four paths, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the six path, dug in to take second late stretch and finished well at the outside flank of the winner. MUAD'DIB stalked from the three path, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole and raced close in the four path on the far turn, though, flattened stride in late yards. JUNGLE BEAST saved ground, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced in the three path on the far turn and flattened stride the final sixteenth. C R'S MANDATE made light contact with Noballstwostrikes leaving the gate, started a bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. CANDY INVASION raced in the five path the first turn, settled well back and could only improve his position. NOBALLSTWOSTRIKES was jostled leaving the gate then rated close inside, challenged at the nine sixteenths pole, dueled at even terms leaving the half mile pole but dropped back and gave chase from the three eighths, raced at the rail on the far turn and weakened. NO LOVE FOR JUBA raced in the six path the opening turn, the three path the second turn and showed little response through the backstretch. LORD OF CORK raced clear into the first turn and rated the pace, came under pressure leaving the nine sixteenths pole and contested mostly even terms from that point, but weakened at the rail on the far turn. MACHEN'S RIDGE raced in the seven path the opening turn, left the second turn outside and never factored.

ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed break,saved ground,bid 5/16,up 3wd mid turn,held on drvng

ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed break,bid 7/16,off rail far turn,evenly lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 10800. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligib ility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAKINLIMMARGARITAS took a quick lead and rated the pace inside, came under pressure approaching the quarter pole, raced at the rail on the turn and was steadily handled in the lane. KATALIMA steadied early then saved ground racing well off the pace, started a bid toward the seven sixteenths pole and steadily improved, raced off the rail on the far turn and dug in to take second under the wire. MISS LAUREN stalked the early pace two deep, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn, dug in under steady stretch handling but was nipped from second under the wire. WOODSONG'S CASTLE saved ground, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and flattened in the lane. BAYS CASTLE raced in the five path the first turn and left the turn outside, gave chase toward the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and showed little more. BOCA BIRDIE was reluctant to load and raced well back saving ground, gave chase approaching the five sixteenths pole, angled to the seven path through the far turn and passed rivals outside. LOOKING FOR FLARE showed little response through the backstretch. HOLY HIP broke a bit rank then saved ground. PUSH was reluctant to load and became fractious in the gate, rated close to the early pace inside, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, faded into the far turn and appeared to hit the rail midway through the turn. MAY MAYS CASTLE raced in the four path the first turn, picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole but faded off the rail on the far turn.
